fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.activation

Interface IRankedServiceEventListener<S>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - service type, normally an interface.
    All Superinterfaces:
    EventListener

    public interface IRankedServiceEventListener<S>
extends EventListener
    Ranked service event listener, providing notifications as services are dynamically added and removed.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IRankedServiceEventContext, createRankedServiceTracker

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Invoked when a service is added.
      void serviceRemoved(Event<IRankedServiceEventContext<S>> event)

    • Method Detail

      • serviceAdded

        void serviceAdded(Event<IRankedServiceEventContext<S>> event)
        Invoked when a service is added.

        Associating the listener with the tracker when the tracker is created ensures that events will also be dispatched for tracked services that were registered before the tracker was created.

        Parameters:
        event - the event, providing access (via the event context) to the ranked service (and in turn, to the service object).
        Since:
        1.0

      • serviceRemoved

        void serviceRemoved(Event<IRankedServiceEventContext<S>> event)
        Invoked when a service is removed.

        When the tracker is closed, an event will also be dispatched for all services that were already tracked.

        Parameters:
        event - the event, providing access (via the event context) to the ranked service (and in turn, to the service object). Note that, as the service object is being unregistered when the event is delivered, usage of the service object should be limited or avoided.
        Since:
        1.0
